ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The class is definitely useful for people who are in (or who intend to go into) graduate programs. Highly recommended.
It's a good review of measure theory, so I guess I would recommend it. But I would only recommend it to someone who really needs to know the subject because it's not exactly a fun course.
Very much recommended. This class will prepare you for anything requiring background in measure theory. It's well taught and well organized and interesting.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course has improved my analysis background. Although I have studied measure theory before, this class has strengthen some of my weak spotsAs I am not yet doing research I cannot say if the course contributed to it.
It helps me for my future preparation in qualifying exam.
It's too early for me to tell whether this course will contribute to my research.
